						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What's the zapper code look like?</div><br />The timing program isn't available yet. But I see the same (lack of) response with the 1-gun Y on-off zapkernel of <a href="http://pineight.com/nes/#ruder" class="postlink">Zap Ruder</a>, which reports how long it takes for the sensor to turn on (go high voltage, or low logic level after running through the controller port's inverter) and then how long to turn off. I point it at my CRT TV and it works wonderfully. I point it at an LCD, no dice.<br /><br />Anyone willing to solder together this photodiode circuit, test it, and ship it to a U.S. address may be eligible for a reward. PM me.</div>

