						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Or is there a difference between the gray Zapper and the later red Zapper that might have the latter to have less filtering?</div><br />If it's anything like its contemporaries, the frequency selectivity of the IR demodulator IC in the Zapper is positively abysmal, without only about 6dB of rejection per octave. I got my red zapper to trigger reliably on light sources from 4kHz to 64kHz, and I strongly suspect it would go wider.</div>

